ApiTotalUsageEventLog.name: ApiTotalUsageEventLog
ApiTotalUsageEventLog.description: API Total Usage Event Log contains details about Platform SOAP API, Platform REST API, and Bulk API requests.

ApiFamily.description: The API family. For example, REST, SOAP, or Bulk.

ApiResource.description: The API method or resource. For example, describeSObjects for SOAP.

ClientIp.description: The IP address of the client that’s using Salesforce services. A Salesforce internal IP, such as a login from AppExchange, is shown as “Salesforce.com IP”. For example: 96.43.144.26.

ClientName.description: The name of the client making the API request.

ConnectedAppIdentifier.description: The ID of the connected app making the API request.

HttpMethod.description: The HTTP method. For example, GET.

IsApiLimitCounted.description: Whether the request counted against the API limit (true) or not (false).

ObjectName.description: The name of the object accessed by the API request.

PlannerIdentifier.description: The ID of the agent planner.

RequestIdentifier.description: The unique ID of a single transaction. A transaction can contain one or more events. Each event in a given transaction has the same RequestIdentifier. For example: 3nWgxWbDKWWDIk0FKfF5DV.

StatusCode.description: The HTTP response status code for the request.

Timestamp.description: The access time of Salesforce services in GMT. For example, 2020-01-20T19:12:26.965Z. Milliseconds are the most granular setting.

UserIdentifier.description: The ID of the user who’s using Salesforce services through the UI or the API. For example: 00530000009M943.
